<h3>I. Page Actions</h3>
<p>Menu for actions associated with the current view. If the user doesn't have permission to add widgets, this menu is displayed as a narrow drop down menu rather than an expanding ribbon.</p>
<ol>
  <li>The gear icon provides access to page actions.</li>
  <li>Clicking slides page menu into view.</li>
  <li>User options for the view are provided. In this scenario (dashboard multi-entry view) user may add space to faves, make the space the home space. If user has permission, other administrative actions may be provided for the current view.</li>
</ol>

<h3>II. Adding Widgets to View</h3>
<p>Action menu showing behaviors for customizing content in views. Showing multi-entry view. If user doesn't have permission to add widgets, they only see the options in II below.</p>
<ol>
  <li>User opens the page actions from primary menu.
    <ol>
      <li>Clicking action icon (gear) displays the Page Menu.</li>
      <li>Customization options are displayed in left of menu.</li>        
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>User selects Article Section
    <ol>
      <li>Article Section dialog opens.</li>
      <li>User enters widget details in form.</li> 
      <li>User submits form.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>New widget displays in page with color animation.</li>
  <li>All movable/editable fields are highlighted in the page.</li>
  <li>User may move the widget within the applicable drop area, e.g. a body widget can be moved up/down or left/right if the body is a mult-column layout.</li>
  <li>If the user has permission, he may be able to quickly change title by clicking on it.</li>
  <li>If the user has permission, he will see an edit icon in the widget title bar on hover. Clicking the edit icon will open the widget editor. Edit icons in normal view are hidden, but may be displayed on hover.</li>
  <li>Collapsing the page actions menu toggles the move actions--highlights are removed and user may no longer move blocks.</li>
  <li>Note: Move action is always visible in the prototype, but should only be available in page action mode.</li>
</ol>

<h3>II. Quick Add</h3>
<p>Behaviors for quick add dialog accessed from top nav.</p>
<ol>
  <li>User clicks the Quick add icon.</li>
  <li>Dialog opens showing types for quick add, e.g. Article, Task, Document, etc.</li>
  <li>User selects type to add. Form for the selected type is displayed.</li>
  <li>Forms display minimum set of fields to quickly add content. If user is viewing a single space, the space is automatically selected in the form.</li>
  <li>Additional fields are hidden from view and must be toggled to display, e.g. Tags, Attachments.</li>
  <li>Note: Space and Tag fields should use design patterns not shown here.</li>
</ol>